    "events": {
        "primary": [
            "Kavya, a shy girl who recently moved to Bengaluru, is nervous to speak at her new school.",
            "On a class trip to a butterfly park, Kavya's teacher, Laila Miss, asks a question about caterpillars.",
            "Kavya summons the courage to answer, sharing her deep knowledge of the butterfly life cycle with her class.",
            "Kavya bonds with her classmate Mary while discussing butterflies and their migration.",
            "She explains her family moved because a drought, which dried up their river, affected the butterflies and their farm.",
            "Kavya compares her own brave journey to that of the small but resilient butterflies and makes a new friend in Mary."
        ],
        "secondary": [
            "Kavya feels overwhelmed and small in the big, noisy city.",
            "Kavya worries that her new classmates will make fun of her accent.",
            "Laila Miss teaches the class about butterfly migration and mud-puddling.",
            "Kavya relates the butterflies' bumpy journey on the wind to her own bus ride to Bengaluru.",
            "The story includes a non-fiction section on how to build a butterfly rest station to help with conservation."
        ]
    },
